                     <p> 
                        <placeName key="place_106093">
                           <supplied>HATFIELD BROAD OAK</supplied>
                        </placeName> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Pervyle</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_106093">Hatfield Regis</placeName>
                        </persName> 
                  grants to <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Schrub</surname>
                        </persName> two acres of land and more,
                  and one piece of land, of which the said two acres and more lie in a field called 
                  '<placeName type="minor">Mecheroysefeld</placeName>,' and the said piece of land lies in
                  <placeName type="minor">Lytylroysefeld</placeName>, in exchange for one croft called 
                  <placeName type="minor">Tayloryscroft</placeName> with a garden adjacent, and for one piece of land lying in
                  <placeName type="minor">Blakelond</placeName>. 
                  Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_106093">Hatfield Regis</placeName> on the feast of St. Valentine, <origDate notBefore="1439-09-01" notAfter="1440-08-31">18 Hen. VI</origDate>. 
                  </p>
